title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1974-10-20
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Mama Tried, Deal, Beat It On Down The Line, Loser, Jack Straw, Tennessee Jed, El Paso, Brokedown Palace, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Around & Around

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Drums*-> Not Fade Away*-> Drums*-> The Other One*-> Wharf Rat*-> Playin' In The Band*

Set 3

Good Lovin'*, It Must Have Been The Roses,Promised Land*, Eyes Of The World-> Stella Blue, Sugar Magnolia*, E: Johnny B. Goode, E: Mississippi Half Step-> We Bid You Good Night

*with Mickey Hart; Last Wall of Sound show; Phil Lesh and Ned Lagin ("Seastones") between sets

reviews.review_text:
Jazz jams I have recently fell in love with 74 era jazz jams sweetly hidden in spots such as Playing in the Band. As a 80's and 90's era head Brent and his bluesy organ style were always my home base. For about a decade now searching up and down the years here on the Archives and prior cassette copies, from 69 Dark Stars to 95 Victim or the Crime's, somehow Keith's contribution went mostly unnoted. I have always been a lover of Donna especially when she goes all "Ella Fitzgerald". Now I am grateful to be having new breath blown into my Dead catalog with an amazing new appreciation for Keith's jazz jam addition to the band. 
-Peace and play Dead
Jack Straw alone ! and WOW. is this the final Loser"Sweet Susie" ?
